<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb51d8b1d-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s421"><num value="421">§ 421.</num><heading> Definition</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this part, the term “executive agency” has the meaning given that term under <ref href="/us/usc/t41/s133">section 133 of title 41</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb51d8b1e-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/296/tVIII/s851">Pub. L. 107–296, title VIII, § 851</ref>, <date date="2002-11-25">Nov. 25, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/2235">116 Stat. 2235</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb51d8b1f-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb51d8b20-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idb51d8b21-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">In text, “<ref href="/us/usc/t41/s133">section 133 of title 41</ref>” substituted for “section 4(1) of the Office of Federal Procurement Policy Act (<ref href="/us/usc/t41/s403/1">41 U.S.C. 403(1)</ref>)” on authority of <ref href="/us/pl/111/350/s6/c">Pub. L. 111–350, § 6(c)</ref>, <date date="2011-01-04">Jan. 4, 2011</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3854">124 Stat. 3854</ref>, which Act enacted Title 41, Public Contracts.</p>
</note>
</notes>
